issue.title: Weight different spending categories for your money
Create downloadable maps to get between locations
Get better hotel data
issue.body: Currently, hotel data is inconsistent with regards to various cities. We need this to be more consistent so we can recommend hotels to the user.

issue.title: IATA Codes
issue.body: The Amadeus api requires IATA codes to identify cities for departures/arrivals however, these aren't standard (For example, you can't use ORD, you must use CHI for Chicago flights). We need a more robust system to map these, or we could use a different API.

issue.title: Scheduling System Improvements
issue.body: Our scheduling system, as of now, pulls a bunch of data from APIs and attempts to schedule events and meal times based on some simple parameters. This scheduling system could be improved by getting data about popularities or how crowded something is and using that to influence the scheduling of a trip.

issue.title: Moment.js to date conversions
issue.body: During scheduling, the moment.js library is use but it offsets our times by 6 hours since we are developing in Central Time. Right now we are using a hard-coded fix but this server should be extensible to other regions

issue.title: A better recommender system
issue.body: Right now, we are using a pretty standard random forest classifier to get potential locations for users. This model could be improved by messing with the parameters or by experimenting with pipelining components and adjusting the model features.

issue.title: Reduce external API dependencies
issue.body: Currently, we are using several APIs which makes parts of the application really slow. Ideally, we can consolidate these calls to our own modules.
